Description:
The Space
Our home is nestled on a quiet hill in Pacific Manor, the northern neighborhood in the charming coast town of Pacifica. The living room has large windows overseeing the Pacific Ocean. On a clear day, you can see from our living room the Farallon Islands, a National Wildlife Refuge--home to a huge seabird colony, seals, whales, and sharks--30 miles off the coast. The backyard offers a steep hill to hike for an even more awesome sunset vista view. This place is ideal for nature lovers, beach lovers, animal lovers (pets welcomed!), couples, surfers, and is LGBT friendly. We are a 3-minute car drive or a brisk .7 mile, 18-minute walk to the ocean.
Interior
The entire interior features high ceilings with exposed wood beams. There are skylights in the bathroom as well as kitchen. Recent renovations include new living room curtains and wood flooring in the kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with appliances for cooking and baking. New wood flooring was installed this summer here is new wood flooring and a dishwasher.
Guest Access
Guests stay in the master bedroom furnished with a queen bed, two side tables, a desk, and a dresser. Common areas include the kitchen, bathroom, backyard, side yard, and large patio deck. We have high-speed internet and also offer our guests access to our desktop during their stay.
Interaction with Guests
We greet all our guests upon arrival and provide a quick tour and set of keys. In the event we may be out of town, our roommate will greet you though we will remain available via phone/email to answer any questions that may arise.
The Neighborhood
Pacifica is a quaint and peaceful town with an abundance of nature, yet close to San Francisco. We are 20 minutes to the Mission or Union Square and 15 minutes to the Outer Mission or Sunset. San Francisco International Airport (SFO) is 16 minutes away. Pacifica has spectacular scenery, trails, and beaches with great surf. Wild animals we have encountered on our block include deer, raccoons, and skunks. The people are friendly and our neighbors mostly comprise of SF professionals and their families.
Parking
There is always ample street parking outside the house.
Other Things to Note
Our roommate is a female in her early 30`s with a Masters in Public Health who works in the wellness industry. When we are out of town, she cares for Homer, our loving, well-trained 6-year-old German Shepard who is recovering from recent hip surgery and sleeps in the living room.
Getting Around
While you may want to walk, hike, and bike to explore Pacifica`s trails and beaches -- getting to our home is best by car. There is easy access to HWY 1 (5 minutes), I-280 (5 minutes), and US 101 (10 minutes). Access to public transportation by car is recommended unless you are an avid cyclist: BART Station is 7 minutes away and San Bruno Caltrain Station is 13 minutes.
House Rules
No shoes inside the house
No smoking inside the house
Front gates must be closed when front door is open, and side door must be kept closed at all times to prevent our beloved dog from straying
